headline: A Look at Alexandria Real Estate Equities’s Valuation After Dividend Freeze and Capital Flexibility Move
summary: Alexandria Real Estate Equities (ARE) just made a move that is sure to catch the attention of investors focused on dividends. The company’s Board of Directors reaffirmed a quarterly cash dividend of $1.32 per share for the third quarter of 2025, opting not to raise the payout further as it has done in the past. By leaving the dividend unchanged, Alexandria is freeing up more than $40 million in liquidity each year. This signals an emphasis on financial flexibility rather than maximizing...
